               <msContents>
                  <summary>Hidāyat al-qavāʼid (Guidance on Administrative Regulations) by Hidāyat
                     Allāh Bihārī, composed in 1126/1714-15 (f. 2r), detailing the duties and
                     functions of the different Mughal offices. </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115922" n="1"
                     xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3996A-item1">
                     <author key="person_f8868">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Hidāyat Allāh Bihārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">هدایت الله بهاری</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23782">Hidāyat al-qavāʼid</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">هدایت القوائد</title>
                     <colophon>(f. 19r): Copied for William Irvine from a manuscript in Jaunpur by
                        ʻAbd al-ʻAzīz of Bhitrī, Saidpur, Ghazipur district on 8 January 1898. </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
